executor_display_name: Send campaign messages via API-triggered delivery
executor_description: Use this endpoint to send immediate, ad-hoc messages to designated users via API-triggered delivery.
Update Live Activity

value.app_id: (required, string) App API identifier retrieved from the Developer Console.
value.activity_id: (required, string) When you register your Live Activity using launchActivity, you use the pushTokenTag parameter to name the Activity’s push token to a custom string. Set activity_id to this custom string to define which Live Activity you want to update.
value.content_state: (required, object) You define the ContentState parameters when you create your Live Activity. Pass the updated values for your ContentState using this object. The format of this request must match the shape you initially defined.
value.end_activity: (optional, boolean) If true, this request ends the Live Activity.
value.dismissal_date: (optional, datetime in ISO-8601 format) The time to remove the Live Activity from the user’s UI. If this time is in the past, the Live Activity will be removed immediately.
value.stale_date: (optional, datetime in ISO-8601 format) The time the Live Activity content is marked as outdated in the user’s UI.
value.notification: (optional, object ) Include an `apple_push` object to define a push notification that creates an alert for the user.

value.fields_to_export: (required, array of string) name of user data fields to export, e.g., ['first_name', 'email', 'purchases']
value.output_format: (optional, string) When using your own S3 bucket, allows to specify file format as 'zip' or 'gzip'. Defaults to zip file format

executor_description: Use this endpoint to record custom events, purchases, and update user profile attributes.
Use this endpoint to add new user aliases for existing identified users, or to create new unidentified users.

value.user_aliases: (required, array of new user alias object)

executor_description: Use this endpoint to export all the users within a segment.
Use this endpoint to export data from any user profile by specifying a user identifier.

value.external_ids: (optional, array of strings) External identifiers for users you wish to export
value.user_aliases: (optional, array of user alias objects) user aliases for users to export
value.device_id: (optional, string) Device identifier as returned by various SDK methods such as `getDeviceId
value.braze_id: (optional, string) Braze identifier for a particular user
value.fields_to_export: (optional, array of strings) Name of user data fields to export. Defaults to all if not provided

executor_description: Use this endpoint to update existing user aliases.

value.aliases_to_identify: (required, array of alias to identify objects)
value.merge_behavior: (optional, string) one of 'none' or 'merge' is expected

executor_description: Use this endpoint to merge one user into another user.

executor_description: Use this endpoint to delete any user profile by specifying a known user identifier.

value.external_ids: (optional, array of string) External ids for the users to delete
value.user_aliases: (optional, array of user alias objects) User aliases for the users to delete
value.braze_ids: (optional, array of string) Braze user identifiers for the users to delete

sampleData.deleted: (required, integer) number of user ids queued for deletion

executor_description: Use this endpoint to rename your users’ external IDs.

executor_description: Use this endpoint to retrieve a series of the number of sessions for your app over a designated time period.

data.time: (string) point in time - as ISO 8601 extended when unit is hour and as ISO 8601 date when unit is day
